We are seeking a technically versatile and self-motivated developer who can work with little supervision in a semi-unstructured environment typical of a small company. Coordinating with support, sales and technical staff, you will be responsible for the further development and maintenance of our web-based CAFM application involving multiple facets including floor plans, database interaction, file I/O, and user interfaces with 3rd party components. Reporting to the CEO who coordinates the company’s software developments, you will be tasked to explore technical solutions to problems on your own. 

We are seeking a senior software developer with at least 7 years experience in web application development and support with database design skills in a Microsoft .NET/SQL. The right candidate will have experience as a lead developer (or proven experience to become one), a thorough understanding of solutions written in C# and VB.NET, and strong debugging skills.
Primary Responsibilities:

Maintain, modify, and in some cases, refactor existing codebase;
Design, build, and maintain efficient, reusable, and reliable VB.NET code;
Design, create, and maintain database schema upgrade scripts that correspond with each software release;
Facilitate integration with other Enterprise Systems by building, maintaining REST & web APIs;
Lead and support architectural changes (including identifying and removing key performance bottlenecks) as customer base migrates applications from on-premises to Cloud-hosted environments; 
Devise and run unit tests before providing builds to QA for further testing;
Participate in requirements, design discussions with IT teams and/or business units, as needed;
Take direction, constructive suggestions and work to specified deadlines, with the ability to execute development code with limited guidance;
Maintain the codebase using source control software, preferably Microsoft Team Foundation Server (TFS);
Interface with lead graphics developer to provide web-driven solutions;
Assist support staff interfacing with customers on high priority technical issues and to understand business process and enhancement requests to assure solutions are useful applications to all Consortium Members.

Required Qualifications:

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science and/or Engineering, or equivalent education and experience;
Experience with ASP.NET Web application using Visual Studio.NET suite (VB.NET);
Experience web application technologies, frameworks such as: jQuery, angular.js, HTML 5, and CSS 3;
Experience with connecting web applications to remote data sources using ADO.NET, ODBC and OLEDB; back-end SQL programming with Oracle and/or SQL Server; and a good understanding  of database schema;
Experience with software development life cycle (SDLC) and ability to effectively convert discussions and enhancement ideas to technical specification;
Experience with SQL and ability to write SQL (T-SQL) queries and scripts. (Oracle, PL/SQL experience a plus).

Desired Qualifications:

Experience with ASP.NET MVC and converting ASP.NET apps to MVC/Razor views;
Solid knowledge of object oriented design and programming including programming in C#;
Experience with Bootstrap, SVG and .NET components from Telerik;
Experience with MS Team Foundation Server and ability to setup, configure and manage TFS instances internally;
Experience with Cloud providers and technologies such as Microsoft Azure and/or AWS;
Some familiarity with the facilities management field and related business processes.
